  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. These typically include:\n\n1. Requirements for financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement internal compliance programs\n\n2. Key legislation examples:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- International: Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n\n3. Penalties can include:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Business license revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\nThese laws aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income and to track potential financial crimes.",
